-- Argentine Stock Movers: Siderar and Tenaris Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-03-14T20:31:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/argentine-stock-movers-siderar-and-tenaris-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.1 percent to 2,709.6.  Tenaris SA (TS)   dropped 1.5 percent to 100.5 pesos, the
biggest decline in a week. The world’s largest producer of
seamless steel tubes used in the oil industry fell in line with
the price of crude.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   fell 1.7 percent to 1.76 pesos, the
lowest in two weeks.  Argentina ’s largest steel producer
retreated in line with the price of base metals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
